<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="465" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="70.[1388,2594,1789,2769]" pageId="70" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1390,1746,2498,2531]" pageId="70" pageNumber="465">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Remy’s Pygmy Shrew has a relatively small distribution but is found in Minkébé National Park in Gabon. It does not seem to face any major threats other than localized habitat loss and degradation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
